com.indeed.status.core

Class AbstractDependency

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.indeed.status.core.AbstractDependency
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Dependency, Documented, Callable<CheckResult>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ComparableDependency, PingableDependency, SimpleDependency

    @ThreadSafe
public abstract class AbstractDependency
extends Object
implements Dependency
    The AbstractDependency provides a convenience base class for implementers of the Dependency interface. All primitive properties are captured here as fields, leaving on the Callable.call() method to be implemented.

      • getServicePool

        public String getServicePool()
        Specified by:
        getServicePool in interface Dependency
        Returns:
        The location where the dependent service/resource exists. This will be helpful especially when those service/resources exists in several places, which means when one of these fails, this helps us detect the location immediately. We could avoid grepping the logs. Examples: "dbpool.example.com:3306/mysqldb1", "ServiceName:ZoneName", etc.
